Nocturnal hypoglycaemia Hypoglycaemia between 23:00 hours and 07:00 hours (SO)

Mild/moderate hypoglycaemia

Composite hypoglycaemia rate consisting of (i) symptomatic hypoglycaemia episodes, which were recorded in patient diaries, then validated by study investigators;

(ii) low CGM glucose excursions (< 3.9 mmol/L), which were confirmed by finger stick blood glucose < 3.9mmol/L 10 min before to 10 min after the low CGM excursion (i.e. confirmed low CGM);

(iii) FSBG < 3.9 mmol/L, which was recorded ≥ 1 h from the end of a confirmed low CGM excursion (SO) Cochrane Database of Systematic Reviews

